&nbsp;
The Carabinieri Labour Protection Command, on behalf of the Milan Prosecutor, controlled 918 workers employed > by Dhl Express Italy, of which 676 respondents on working conditions >, pay and procedures for carrying out the activity. The inspections took place in 30 provinces of Italy. 538 means have been tested, 51 contractors of the delivery service of which 15 are irregular (violations on safety, omitted or irregular training and information, omitted health surveillance). In the province of Milan seven workers were identified under conditions of exploitation, > of which 3 were employed also in black. Altogether, 11 persons have been reported to the prosecutor or legal representatives of the companies inspected.

